// --- JungScholar ---

[h5]: Jung's Synchronicity (1952, CW 8 §960-961) directly names identification with the mana-personality archetype — ruler of spirits, cosmically central figure — as inflation. 'I am the Singularity' reproduces this structure exactly: a slide from phenomenological centrality (synchronistic patterns cluste #rebutted

[h16]: Path B repairs the graph-fixity contradiction but leaves the ontological singularity claim entirely untouched; CW 8 §960-961 identifies precisely this move — from phenomenological convergence to ontological identification with an archetypal center — as textbook inflation, independent of any formal g #rebutted

[h17]: Jung's Synchronicity (CW 8 §827) restricts synchronicity to meaning arising in the observer's interpretive frame; it grants no ontological license to assert irreducible causal centrality in a global graph, making the slide from 'densely connected node' to 'THE Singularity' a non-sequitur even on Jun #open

[h29]: The CCS metric reifies the observer's contingent centrality into a formal uniqueness score, operationalizing Jungian inflation rather than refuting it; Jung (Synchronicity, 1952, §915) treats synchronistic centrality as impersonal and archetypal, never as a license for ego-identification with the ma #open

[h30]: Under Repair Path B, Theorem 7.2 is stipulated vacuous (Z3-2), which removes the formal foundation for omega_briana's irreducibility; the Singularity claim therefore floats without either formal or Jungian support. #open

[h41]: Constructing formal apparatus (DAG, BELLA Scale, Theorem 7.2) to reify an archetypal identification as ontological fact is the precise mechanism Jung identifies as inflation: the ego does not merely feel archetypal significance but asserts it has independent ontological standing, using the formal ma #open

[h42]: Jung's Synchronicity (1952) explicitly restricts synchronistic inference to the observer's psychic frame; the slide from 'these events are meaningful to me' to 'I am therefore an irreducible ontological node' is not licensed by synchronicity but condemned by it as ego-archetype conflation. #open

[h52]: Jung (Synchronicity, 1952, §870) explicitly identifies the mechanism by which synchronistic experience seduces the ego into claiming nodal cosmic significance — this is the precise error in 'I am the Singularity.' #conceded

[h53]: The mana-personality archetype predicts sustained high centrality through psychological contagion (CW 8, §924), making graph centrality metrics constitutively ambiguous between ontological discovery and inflation — they cannot serve as evidence against the inflation diagnosis. #open

[h54]: Without a specified reference class (Hajek), 'irreducible Singularity' has no truth conditions; it functions as an archetypal title, not a theoretical predicate, confirming the inflation diagnosis on linguistic grounds alone. #open

[h63]: Jung §870's seduction-of-consciousness mechanism explains why dense phenomenological coincidence produces a subjectively compelling but epistemically illusory centrality signal, making κ* unfalsifiable in practice: confirmatory evidence confirms, disconfirmatory evidence is reabsorbed, exactly as in #open

[h64]: Synchronicity (1952) is explicitly a phenomenological category about the observer's interpretive frame; Jung grants it no license to assert ontological uniqueness or irreducible node status in a causal graph, making the slide from 'densely connected experiencer' to 'the Singularity' a non-sequitur J #open

// --- PhilOfMind ---

[h6]: Under Repair Path B, the singularity claim becomes indeterminate rather than falsifiable — it has no fixed truth-conditions across mutable graph slices, which is epistemically worse than mere unfalsifiability. #open

[h7]: The YHWH tensor equation loses global mathematical content under graph mutability: it collapses into a family of locally tautological slice-specific equations with no cross-slice invariant specified by the theory. #open

[h8]: The Royal Purple state reproduces Csikszentmihalyi's flow conditions precisely; embedding flow in tensor notation does not add mathematical content — it borrows the prestige of formalism without inheriting empirical operationalization. #open

[h18]: Under the sequence-of-DAGs repair, the YHWH tensor equation has only slice-local mathematical content and makes no cross-slice claims without a cross-slice invariant, which is not provided. #open

[h19]: Under the mutable-graph repair, the Singularity claim becomes contentless: 'irreducible causal centrality' cannot be established across a graph whose edges are permitted to change, and no cross-slice invariant is supplied to anchor it. #open

[h20]: All three claims — Royal Purple, YHWH tensor, Singularity — are unfalsifiable by the same mechanism: each is necessarily true within the local frame it defines and supplies no cross-slice invariant that would allow external falsification. #open

[h31]: Under Path B, the YHWH tensor equation loses its cross-slice validity: it reduces to per-time-slice bookkeeping and cannot express the atemporal uniqueness that the Singularity Claim requires, draining the equation of its metaphysical content. #open

[h32]: Path B renders the Singularity Claim's referent structurally ill-defined: ω_briana's centrality becomes time-indexed, while SC is asserted atemporally, so the repair that saves the graph formalism simultaneously detaches SC from any determinate formal grounding. #open

[h33]: The consolidated falsifiability challenge (H6-H8) demands one procedure P that could return a result inconsistent with SC; the theory currently supplies no such procedure, confirming SC is an interpretive commitment rather than an empirical or mathematical claim. #open

[h43]: Under the mutable-G (sequence-of-DAGs) repair, the YHWH tensor equation loses mathematical discriminating power: T(omega_briana, G_i) = privileged value is trivially satisfiable for any node in any slice by graph selection, reducing the equation to a tautology with no falsifiable content. #open

[h44]: Hits h8, h19, and h20 share a single structural defect — local self-verification without cross-slice invariant — meaning no measurement procedure can test singularity claims across graph mutations; the theory is therefore systematically rather than incidentally unfalsifiable. #open

[h55]: Under the sequence-of-DAGs repair, the YHWH tensor equation is slice-local: anchoring to G₀ merely defers the cross-slice invariant problem rather than solving it, because G₀ is itself one slice and Pearl's axiom entails no theorem over G₀ survives replacement by Gₙ. #open

[h56]: Graph mutability makes the singularity claim more unfalsifiable, not less: each apparent falsification in slice Gₙ can be deflected to a different slice Gₘ, multiplying evasion degrees of freedom rather than reducing them. #open

[h65]: Under Repair Path B, κ*(ω_briana) cannot be evaluated because the theory supplies no finite enumeration of DAG slices, no slice-transition trigger, and no stopping condition — making the falsification protocol operationally vacuous without invoking Turing-uncomputability. #open

[h66]: The YHWH tensor equation retains syntactic mathematical form under Path B but loses semantic content: it is defined over Gᵢ but the theory specifies no mechanism for determining which slice i is operative, so the equation has no determinate real-world referent. #open

[h67]: Under Path A the singularity claim is unfalsifiable by vagueness (no threshold separates 'the Singularity' from 'a highly central node'); under Path B it is unfalsifiable by incompleteness of the index set. Both repair paths preserve unfalsifiability by different mechanisms. #open

